{"id":511085773,"lang":"java","time":"8Â months","timestamp":1624279483,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/511085773/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"39.3 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode() {}\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        ListNode p = l1;\n        ListNode q = l2;\n        ListNode dummyHead = new ListNode(0);\n        ListNode current = dummyHead;\n        int carry = 0;\n        while(p != null || q != null){\n            int x = (p != null) ? p.val : 0;\n            int y = (q != null) ? q.val : 0;\n              \n            int sum = x + y + carry;\n            carry = sum / 10;\n            current.next = new ListNode(sum % 10);\n            current = current.next;\n            if (p != null) p = p.next;\n            if (q != null) q = q.next;\n        }\n        if(carry > 0) {\n            current.next = new ListNode(carry);\n        }\n        return dummyHead.next;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers"}
